    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for this house i'm buying in toronto. what actually is escrow and why can't i just pay the seller directly?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "In Toronto, an escrow account is a neutral third-party account that holds funds until certain conditions are met in a real estate transaction. The seller typically transfers ownership of the property to you once the escrow funds are released, and this helps ensure that all trades and payments are made on time.\nYou can't just pay the seller directly because it doesn't provide a clear record of payment and doesn't ensure that the funds are being held securely until all conditions of the sale are met.\nThis set-up also helps protect both you and the seller from potential disputes or delays in the transaction.",
