    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay that makes sense. so basically someone else is just sitting on the money while the paperwork happens? who usually manages that account, like a lawyer or a bank? and does it cost much to set up?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "In Ontario, Canada, the registered title company or lawyer typically manages the escrow account. They verify the documents, hold the funds, and release them when the conditions of the sale are met.\nAs for the cost, setting up an escrow account can involve a one-time fee, which varies depending on the title company or lawyer. Typically, it's a flat fee ranging from $200 to $1,000, depending on the transaction type and the size of the purchase.\nThis cost is usually paid by the buyer and is a standard part of the home buying process in Toronto.",
      "source": "target",
