      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To minimize the risk of mismanagement or loss, the lawyer or title company is required to maintain a flawless track record, undergo regular audits, and adhere to strict security measures.\nIn Canada, there are also government regulations and industry standards that govern escrow services, ensuring that they are held in trust by a third-party trustee and strictly adhering to specific protocols.\nAdditionally, the lawyer or title company typically holds the money in a separate, interest-bearing account, and releases funds only when the sale is complete and all parties have signed off on the transfer.",
